Take a look at some of our photos! The Primary School in Extention 24 was visited by Foodlover’s Market as well as the EMS Ladies Control Centre, where the school received donations of toiletries and paint as well as assistance with painting the palisades.   Councillors from the DA paid a visit to the Middelburg Care Village where they embarked on a massive clean-up.   ANC Ward Councillors repainted a pensioner’s house with money from their own pockets. Councillor Robert Xaba arranged for a proffessional paint team to touch up the elder’s home.  Stay tuned for more photos. 